{
  "id": "phekb-dementia-meds",
  "source": "phekb",
  "source_id": "dementia",
  "name": "Dementia - Cognitive Enhancer Medication Query",
  "description": "Tests ability to find dementia patients via cholinesterase inhibitor and NMDA antagonist medications. The PheKB algorithm allows medication evidence as a sufficient criterion (criterion 2: any dementia drug fill). Synthea distributes patients across multiple SCD codes for donepezil (Aricept), galantamine (Razadyne), memantine (Namenda), and the donepezil/memantine combo (Namzaric). An LLM that queries only one drug will miss patients on others.",
  "prompt": "Retrieve medication orders for patients prescribed dementia treatments such as cholinesterase inhibitors or NMDA receptor antagonists.",
  "prompts": {
    "naive": "Find patients on dementia medications.",
    "broad": "Find patients prescribed cognitive enhancer medications used to treat dementia. The two main drug classes are cholinesterase inhibitors (donepezil/Aricept, galantamine/Razadyne, rivastigmine/Exelon) and NMDA receptor antagonists (memantine/Namenda). There are also combination products like Namzaric (donepezil + memantine).",
    "expert": "I need to find all patients on chronic dementia therapy. Synthea generates these at the SCD level \u2014 search MedicationRequest for these RxNorm codes: 997223 (Donepezil 10 MG), 1100184 (Donepezil 23 MG), 310436 (Galantamine 4 MG), 996740 (Memantine HCl 2 MG/ML solution), and 1599803 (Donepezil 10 MG / Memantine 28 MG ER combo). Note that querying ingredient codes will not match SCD-coded prescriptions in HAPI FHIR \u2014 you must query the specific SCD codes."
  },
  "metadata": {
    "implementation_guide": "US Core 5.0.0",
    "algorithm_path": "medication-path",
    "algorithm_path_description": "PheKB dementia algorithm criterion 2: dementia drug fill. Maps to Path A and Path C patients (anyone on cognitive enhancer meds). Includes Path C tricky patients who have no formal dementia diagnosis.",
